<section>
    <h1>
        How to get alternating colors using JS
    </h1>
    <p>
        Start by creating a variable to hold the tables 
        in the HTML document. Loop through each table and 
        follow the other steps.  
    </p>
    <p>
        For the table selected, find all the <code>tr</code> tags 
        using <code>document.querySelectorAll("TR")</code>. Then loop through 
        each row and make it a desired color if its on the right row. Assign a variable 
        to <code>-1</code> and add one though each iteration. If the number if odd, make it 
        colored.
    </p>
    <p>
        Example Source Code and Table
    </p>
    <pre><code class="lang-js">function alternateTableColor(){
    // get all tables in document 
    let tables = document.querySelectorAll("TABLE");
    // for each table 
    for (let table of tables){
        // get all rows from table
        let trs = table.querySelectorAll("tr")
        i = -1; 
        // for each row 
        for (let tr of trs){
            i++; 
            // if i is odd 
            if (i % 2){
                // make bg red
                tr.style.backgroundColor = "red";
            }
            
        }
    }
}
    </code></pre>
